  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4416",
  "title": "source map link doesn't work with jsDelivr because of absolute URL",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nJSDelivr on this file: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@4.5.0/dist/instantsearch.production.min.js has at the end `//# sourceMappingURL=instantsearch.production.min.js.map`. This should mean a relative file, but in some cases this seems to be interpreted as an absolute URL and the source map loaded is `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.production.min.js.map`\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://xo94wl403z.csb.app\r\n2. open network panel\r\n3. see http 404\r\n\r\n<img width=\"503\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-05-20 at 11 51 05\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6270048/82432348-37c75580-9a90-11ea-9ad7-99fd12deca55.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:** https://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/create-instantsearch-app/tree/templates/instantsearch.js (yes, the default link has this issue)\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->\r\n\r\nsource maps are loaded relatively and not absolutely\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\n\r\nI think jsDelivr somehow might be responsible for this, but not sure yet, would need to experiment if the default maybe is absolute URL and the link it should say is `./instantsearch.production.min.js.map` instead\r\n",
